[14]:

def fn_build(features_shape, label_shape, **hp):
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Dense(units=features_shape[0], activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))
    model.add(Dense(units=hp['neuron_count'], activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform'))
    model.add(Dense(units=label_shape[0], activation='softmax'))
    return model

[15]:

def fn_train(model, optimizer samples_train, samples_evaluate, **hp):
    model.compile(
        loss = 'categorical_crossentropy'
        , optimizer = optimizer
        , metrics = ['accuracy']
    )
    model.fit(
        samples_train["features"]
        , samples_train["labels"]
        , validation_data = (
            samples_evaluate["features"]
            , samples_evaluate["labels"]
        )
        , verbose = 0
        , batch_size = hp['batch_size']
        , epochs = hp['epoch_count']
        , callbacks=[History()]
    )
    return model

[16]:

hyperparameters = {
    "neuron_count": [9, 12]
    , "batch_size": [3]
    , "learning_rate": [0.03, 0.05]
    , "epoch_count": [30, 60]
}

[19]:

batch = aiqc.Experiment.make(
    library = "keras"
    , analysis_type = "classification_multi"
    , fn_build = fn_build
    , fn_train = fn_train
    , splitset_id = splitset.id
    , encoderset_id = splitset.encodersets[0]
    , repeat_count = 1
    , hide_test = False
    , hyperparameters = hyperparameters

    , fn_optimize = None #automated
    , fn_predict = None #automated
    , fn_loss = None #automated
    , foldset_id = None
)

def fn_optimize(**hp):
    optimizer = keras.optimizers.Adamax()
    return optimizer

def fn_build(features_shape, label_shape, **hp):
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Dense(units=features_shape[0], activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.2))
    model.add(Dense(units=hp['neuron_count'], activation='relu', kernel_initializer='he_uniform'))

def fn_train(model, optimizer, samples_train, samples_evaluate, **hp):
    model.compile(
        loss = 'categorical_crossentropy'
        , optimizer = optimizer
        , metrics = ['accuracy']
    )
    model.fit(
        samples_train["features"]
        , samples_train["labels"]
        , validation_data = (
            samples_evaluate["features"]
            , samples_evaluate["labels"]
        )
        , verbose = 0
        , batch_size = hp['batch_size']
        , epochs = hp['epoch_count']
        , callbacks=[History()]
    )
    return model
